nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Serine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: Multiple convergent prebiotic pathways to serine through five hub molecules: formaldehyde, glycolaldehyde, hydroxypyruvate, glycine, and HCN. Hydrothermal CO\u2082 fixation on iron-sulfur minerals generates C1-C3 intermediates (formate, formaldehyde, pyruvate, glyoxylate). These feed into surface-environment Strecker synthesis, formose-aldol chemistry, and reductive amination routes. Biochemical-stage assembly completes the final amination and hydrolysis steps. Ten distinct pathways ensure chemical redundancy and plausibility across varied early-Earth settings.\n\nMOLECULES (18 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_004: H2O (water) [starting]\n  - mol_005: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_007: CHO2- (formate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C2H4O2 (glycolaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C3H6N2O (serine aminonitrile) [intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C3H4O4 (hydroxypyruvate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C2H5NO2 (glycine) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C3H7NO3 (serine) [target]\n  - mol_013: CO (carbon monoxide) [starting]\n  - mol_014: C3H6O3 (glyceraldehyde) [intermediate]\n  - mol_015: C2H2O3 (glyoxylate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_016: C3H4O3 (pyruvate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_017: C2H4N2 (aminoacetonitrile) [intermediate]\n  - mol_018: H2S (hydrogen sulfide) [starting]\n\nREACTIONS (18 nodes):\n  - rxn_001: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_007 (CO\u2082 hydrogenation to formate on greigite) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_002: mol_007, mol_002 -> mol_006, mol_004 (Formate reduction to formaldehyde on magnetite) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_003: mol_013, mol_002 -> mol_006 (Fischer-Tropsch synthesis of formaldehyde from CO) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_004: mol_006, mol_006 -> mol_008 (Aldol condensation of formaldehyde to glycolaldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_005: mol_008, mol_005, mol_003 -> mol_009, mol_004 (Strecker synthesis of serine aminonitrile from glycolaldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_006: mol_009, mol_004 -> mol_012 (Hydrolysis of serine aminonitrile to serine) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_007: mol_006, mol_005, mol_003 -> mol_017, mol_004 (Strecker synthesis of aminoacetonitrile from formaldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_008: mol_017, mol_004 -> mol_011 (Hydrolysis of aminoacetonitrile to glycine) [Surface]\n  - rxn_009: mol_011, mol_006 -> mol_012 (Glycine hydroxymethylation to serine) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_010: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_016, mol_004 (Hydrothermal CO\u2082 reduction to pyruvate on greigite) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_011: mol_016, mol_004 -> mol_010 (UV-driven hydroxylation of pyruvate to hydroxypyruvate) [Surface]\n  - rxn_012: mol_010, mol_003 -> mol_012, mol_004 (Reductive amination of hydroxypyruvate to serine) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_013: mol_006 -> mol_014 (Formose reaction: formaldehyde to glyceraldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_014: mol_014 -> mol_010 (Oxidation of glyceraldehyde to hydroxypyruvate) [Surface]\n  - rxn_015: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_015, mol_004 (Hydrothermal CO\u2082 reduction to glyoxylate on pyrite) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_016: mol_015, mol_003 -> mol_011, mol_004 (Reductive amination of glyoxylate to glycine) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_017: mol_015, mol_006, mol_003 -> mol_012, mol_004 (One-pot aldol-amination of glyoxylate with formaldehyde to serine) [Surface]\n  - rxn_018: mol_008, mol_001, mol_003, mol_002 -> mol_012, mol_004 (Direct hydrothermal carboxylation-amination of glycolaldehyde to serine) [Hydrothermal]\n\nPATHWAYS (10):\n  - P1: Hydrothermal CO\u2082 \u2192 Formate \u2192 Formaldehyde \u2192 Glycolaldehyde \u2192 Strecker Serine (5 steps)\n  - P2: Fischer-Tropsch Formaldehyde \u2192 Glycolaldehyde \u2192 Strecker Serine (4 steps)\n  - P3: Hydrothermal Pyruvate \u2192 Hydroxypyruvate \u2192 Reductive Amination to Serine (3 steps)\n  - P4: CO\u2082 \u2192 Formaldehyde \u2192 Strecker Glycine \u2192 Hydroxymethylation to Serine (5 steps)\n  - P5: Fischer-Tropsch \u2192 Strecker Glycine \u2192 Hydroxymethylation to Serine (4 steps)\n  - P6: CO\u2082 \u2192 Formaldehyde \u2192 Formose Glyceraldehyde \u2192 Hydroxypyruvate \u2192 Serine (5 steps)\n  - P7: Fischer-Tropsch \u2192 Formose Glyceraldehyde \u2192 Hydroxypyruvate \u2192 Serine (4 steps)\n  - P8: Hydrothermal Glyoxylate \u2192 Glycine \u2192 Serine via Hydroxymethylation (3 steps)\n  - P9: Glyoxylate + Formaldehyde One-Pot Aldol-Amination to Serine (4 steps)\n  - P10: Direct Hydrothermal Carboxylation-Amination of Glycolaldehyde to Serine (4 steps)\n\nHUB MOLECULES: mol_006, mol_008, mol_010, mol_011, mol_015\nCONVERGENCE POINTS: 5\n\n\nPlease evaluate the network and respond with JSON:\n{\n    \"pathway_evaluations\": [\n        {\n            \"pathway_id\": \"<id>\",\n            \"reaction_scores\": {\"rxn_001\": 0.85, ...},\n            \"chemical_feasibility\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"pathway_coherence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"environmental_progression\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"target_achievement\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"overall_confidence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"feedback\": \"<pathway-specific feedback>\",\n            \"approved\": <true if confidence >= 0.8>,\n            \"problematic_reactions\": [\"rxn_ids with issues\"],\n            \"suggestions\": [\"improvements\"]\n        }\n    ],\n    \"best_pathway_id\": \"<id of best pathway>\",\n    \"overall_confidence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n    \"network_feedback\": \"<overall assessment>\",\n    \"approved\": <true if any pathway approved>,\n    \"hub_quality\": <0.0-1.0>,\n    \"convergence_quality\": <0.0-1.0>\n}\n", "raw_response": "{\n  \"pathway_evaluations\": [\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P1\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_001\": 0.90,\n        \"rxn_002\": 0.70,\n   