ported routes. Overall, the network achieves its goal of producing serine through multiple validated prebiotic routes with good environmental progression.\",\n  \"approved\": true,\n  \"hub_quality\": 0.88,\n  \"convergence_quality\": 0.86\n}", "parsed_response": {"pathway_evaluations": [{"pathway_id": "P1", "reaction_scores": {"rxn_001": 0.9, "rxn_003": 0.7, "rxn_004": 0.84, "rxn_005": 0.88, "rxn_006": 0.85}, "chemical_feasibility": 0.78, "pathway_coherence": 0.85, "environmental_progression": 0.9, "target_achievement": 0.85, "overall_confidence": 0.82, "feedback": "Clean Hydrothermal\u2192Surface\u2192Biochemical progression. The formate-to-formaldehyde reduction (rxn_003) is the weakest link \u2014 thermodynamically uphill and experimentally only weakly supported. The Strecker sequence from glycolaldehyde is well-established. Mineral catalyst for aldol (rxn_004) should be specified (e.g., borate, CaCO\u2083).", "approved": true, "problematic_reactions": ["rxn_003"], "suggestions": ["Specify mineral catalyst for rxn_004 (e.g., borate minerals to channel selectivity)", "Consider citing Ritson & Sutherland 2012 for photoreductive formaldehyde generation as alternative to rxn_003"]}, {"pathway_id": "P2", "reaction_scores": {"rxn_002": 0.76, "rxn_004": 0.84, "rxn_005": 0.88, "rxn_006": 0.85}, "chemical_feasibility": 0.8, "pathway_coherence": 0.86, "environmental_progression": 0.88, "target_achievement": 0.85, "overall_confidence": 0.84, "feedback": "Shorter pathway with good H\u2192S\u2192B flow. FTT synthesis of formaldehyde (rxn_002) is plausible but formaldehyde is not the dominant FTT product \u2014 selectivity is a concern. The rest of the pathway is chemically robust. Overall a strong route.", "approved": true, "problematic_reactions": ["rxn_002"], "suggestions": ["Specify mineral catalyst (e.g., Ni-Fe alloy or awaruite) for rxn_002", "Address selectivity for formaldehyde vs. methanol or methane in FTT"]}, {"pathway_id": "P3", "reaction_scores": {"rxn_015": 0.68